Disks -> Drive Settings -> Enable Write Cache

sudo apt install tlp	(battery optimizer)
sudo tlp-stat -s  	(autostart at each boot)

cat /proc/sys/vm/swappiness
sudo gedit /etc/sysctl.conf
Type at the end of file: vm.swapness=10

cd /etc/UPower/
sudo gedit UPower.conf 
PercentageLow=20
Change noti alert from 10% to 20% when battery percentage is low 

sudo passwd wc(Ubuntu username)(~/home/wc) #to change password
After reboot, old password must be typed as final time.

cat /etc/lsb-release (to find current OS version)
top (show CPU Usage, Memory Usage, Process)  'q' to quit
lscpu (CPU detail info)

ping google.com
poweroff	reboot


